    • Constructor Detail

      • LoraTransmission

        public LoraTransmission​(NetworkEntity sender,
                        NetworkEntity receiver,
                        java.lang.Integer transmissionPower,
                        java.lang.Integer bandwidth,
                        java.lang.Integer spreadingFactor,
                        LoraWanPacket content)
        A constructor generating a transmission with a given sender, receiver, transmission power, bandwidth, spreading factor, environment and content.
        Parameters:
        sender - The sender sending the transmission.
        receiver - The receiver receiving the transmission.
        transmissionPower - The transmission power of the transmission.
        bandwidth - The bandwidth of the transmission.
        spreadingFactor - The spreading factor of the transmission.
        content - The content of the transmission.
        Post:
        If the given transmission power is valid, it is set to that power., If the given transmission power is not valid, it is set to 0., If the given bandwidth is valid, it is set to that bandwidth., If the given bandwidth is not valid, it is set to 0., If the given spreading factor is valid, it is set to that spreading factor., If the given spreading factor is not valid, it is set to 0., If the given sender and receiver have the same environment the xPos is set to the given x position., If the given sender and receiver have the same environment the yPos is set to the given y position., If the given sender and receiver have the same environment the environment is set to the given environment., If the given sender and receiver have the same environment the sender is set to the given sender., If the given sender and receiver have the same environment the receiver is set to the given receiver., If the given sender and receiver have a different environment the environment is se to null., If the given sender and receiver have a different environment the sender is set to null., If the given sender and receiver have a different environment the receiver is set to null., If the given sender and receiver have a different environment the xPos is set to 0., If the given sender and receiver have a different environment the yPos is set to 0.
        Effect:
        The departure time is set to LocalTime.now().

      • moveTo

        private void moveTo​(java.lang.Integer xPos,
                    java.lang.Integer yPos)
        Moves a transmission to a given position, while adapting the transmission power.
        Parameters:
        xPos - The x-coordinate of the destination.
        yPos - The y-coordinate of the destination.
        Effect:
        If the destination is more than 0 moves away from the current position, decrease the transmissionPower according to the model and the characteristics of the next position. Which is the position 1 move in the direction of the longest difference or in the x direction if the difference is equal.
